result.execSummary:
The defendant Nathan C Goldsmith was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Strangulation and Suffocation [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.235(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Nathan C Goldsmith in court, in custody, with attorney Ronald James Sonderhouse.   Kevin M. Osborne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Prosecuting Attorney moves to strike repeater from Count 1, Court grants motion. Repeater struck from Count 1. Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 1, Court conducts plea colloquy. Court finds defendant guilty. Count 2 and Count 3 are dismissed and read in. 

Court orders the following: 
- Total sentence: 4.5 years (Initial Confinement: 2.5 years, Extended Supervision: 2 years) 88 Days of Credit if revoked. STAYED
- Defendant IS eligible for Substance Abuse Program
- 2 years Probation
- Court costs of $368.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation.
- DNA Surcharge waived
- DNA Sample waived
- Conditions of Probation: Submit to an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment/counseling. Maintain absolute sobriety/Random UAs. Follow through with any treatment/counseling recommended by Agent. Maintain full-time employment and/or school. Defendant to obtain GED.  Attend a minimum of 2 self help meetings per week. 


CONDITION TIME: 6 Months - The first three months are to be served as straight time and the last 3 months - NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - To commence Forthwith.
